cannery.leafia.pwr=Pressurized Water Reactor
cannery.leafia.pwr.0=The PWR (LWR) is a fully modular multiblock reactor.
cannery.leafia.pwr.1=PWRs in NTM Cursed behaves quite different from the original.
cannery.leafia.pwr.2=These are 3 skins of PWR Fuel Rods to choose from.
cannery.leafia.pwr.3=There are no functional differences, but they have different recipes.
cannery.leafia.pwr.4=PWR Fuel rods accepts generic nuclear fuel items.
cannery.leafia.pwr.5=Fuels can be either inserted by clicking directly on the block or via terminal block.
cannery.leafia.pwr.6=Fuels also can be extracted directly via use of a Screwdriver.
cannery.leafia.pwr.7=PWR Fuel Rods receives 1/2 flux from the §dcorners§r..
cannery.leafia.pwr.8=..and 1/(2^(distance/2-1)) flux from §a4 §acardinal §adirections§r.
cannery.leafia.pwr.9=PWR control rods can be used in path of neutrons to control flux.
cannery.leafia.pwr.a=Lead control rods are cheaper but they move slower.
cannery.leafia.pwr.b=PWR Coolant Channels use up heat from fuel rods to heat up Coolant.
cannery.leafia.pwr.c=It also moderates neutrons that passes through, significantly boosting fission reaction.
cannery.leafia.pwr.d=Graphite blocks also can be used to moderate neutrons.
cannery.leafia.pwr.e=PWR Fuel Rods can be stacked to increase fuel efficiency.
cannery.leafia.lftr=Liquid Fluoride Thorium Reactor
cannery.leafia.lftr.0=The LFTR (MSR) is a modular multiblock reactor.
cannery.leafia.lftr.1=LFTRs use liquid fuel with dynamic mixture and temperature.
cannery.leafia.lftr.2=The fluid will heat up, and the heat can be spent on a Coolant Heat Exchanger.
cannery.leafia.lftr.3=Initially, supported LFTR coolants don't contain any fuel.
cannery.leafia.lftr.4=Fuels can be mixed into LFTR coolants using Mixing Vat.
cannery.leafia.lftr.5=The dynamic mixture system make use of NBTs, which is not supported on normal fluid ducts..
cannery.leafia.lftr.6=..which means, the LFTR, the Mixing Vat (in nuclear mode), the Coolant Heat Exchanger, and the Salt Fuel Separation Plant all requires Special Pipe to transfer fuel liquid.
cannery.leafia.lftr.7=LFTR Reaction Chambers receive flux from 6 cardinal directions..
cannery.leafia.lftr.8=..and these shown 12 extra positions.
cannery.leafia.lftr.9=If one exceeds 6000°C, the component will be destroyed.
cannery.leafia.lftr.a=LFTR Control Rods can be sticked on any side of Reaction Chambers to restrict fission reaction.
cannery.leafia.lftr.b=They can be controlled either manually using Screwdrivers, or via Custom Control Panels.
cannery.leafia.lftr.c=Graphite blocks can be used to moderate neutron flux for more fission reaction.
cannery.leafia.lftr.d=PWR Neutron Reflectors can be used to reflect neutrons to reaction chamber itself.
cannery.leafia.lftr.e=LFTR Arbitrary blocks will mimic other blocks' behavior, while retaining the ability to contain fuel and transfer them to neighboring components.
cannery.leafia.lftr.f=LFTR Fuel Plug has a port on one side that accepts fuel, and emergency port on the bottom.
cannery.leafia.lftr.g=The emergency port will melt at 4000°C, draining (leaking) fuel from your reactor as quickly as possible.
cannery.leafia.lftr.h=Keep in mind that the drain will not work if the bottom port is blocked like this.
