desc.leafia.zirnox.tips.coolant=§3Coolant§r$  CO₂ transfers heat of your fuels to the hull of the reactor.$  The efficiency of this cooling is greatly affected by pressure.$  CO₂ is never consumed by the reactor itself.$§9Feedwater§r$  Hull heat is then used to boil feedwater into steam.$  The fewer water the tank holds, the slower the hull is cooled and the steam produced.
